Arundel MS. 507. Paper, with occasional vellum sonos, 10:4¹-in. by offin. Sec. XV. “ Ex dono Henr. Howard Norfolciensis.’' In different hands, mostly late and irregular. The MS. is probably Northern, since the M.E. tracts (eg. ff. 48, 49) are in the Northern dialect, and f. 50 has a “Tractatus domini Iohannis de Caterigis monachi Ebor.‘’
